speech.p:
I have the honour to present a petition that has been signed by 100 residents of my constituency, who live in one of the rural areas there. It reads: That the non-rural population of these islands has become distanced from the realities of meat, egg, milk production and pest control. Wherefore your Petitioners pray that your honourable House;
(i) takes notice of the concerns expressed by those who marched on 1st March, 1998;
(ii) endeavours to keep animals and animal welfare in perspective,
(iii) refrains from interfering with traditional British rural pastimes such as foxhunting.
And your petitioners, as in duty bound, will ever pray.
